article.headline: Coll. of Charleston 89, UNC-Greensboro 73
article.story: CHARLESTON, S.C. -- Tony White Jr. scored 17 points, leading four College of Charleston players in double figures in a 89-73 win over North Carolina-Greensboro on Thursday night. Jermaine Johnson added 16 points, Donavan Monroe scored 15 and Andrew Goudelock had 13 for the Cougars (16-4, 8-2 Southern Conference). White was a perfect 5-for-5 from beyond the arc, and Goudelock was 3-for-4 from long range. The Cougars hit 13 of 22 3-point attempts compared to the Spartans, who hit just 2 of 10. Ben Stywall led the Spartans (3-16, 2-8) with 26 points and nine rebounds, while Damian Eargle scored 22. It was the fourth loss in a row for the Spartans, who trailed the Cougars 55-37 at the half. Charleston shot 55.6 percent from the field (35 of 63) in the game compared to a 41.8 mark (28 of 67) for the Spartans.
